Let's write the entire file content:

export const recite = (initialBottlesCount, takeDownCount) => {
  if (typeof initialBottlesCount !== 'number' || typeof takeDownCount !== 'number') {
    throw new Error('Parameters must be numbers');
  }
  const verses = [];
  const end = initialBottlesCount - takeDownCount + 1;
  for (let i = initialBottlesCount; i >= end; i--) {
    const firstLine = `${i} ${i === 1 ? 'bottle' : 'bottles'} of beer on the wall, ${i} ${i === 1 ? 'bottle' : 'bottles'} of beer.`;
    let secondLine;
    if (i === 1) {
      secondLine = "Take it down and pass it around, no more bottles of beer on the wall.";
    } else {
      secondLine = `Take one down and pass it around, ${i - 1} ${i - 1 === 1 ? 'bottle' : 'bottles'} of beer on the wall.`;
    }
    verses.push(`${firstLine}\n${secondLine}`);
  }
  const result = verses.join('\n\n') + '\n\nNo more bottles of beer on the wall, no more bottles of beer.\nGo to the store and buy some more, 99 bottles of beer on the wall.';
  return result;
};

Check for off-by-one: If initial=99, takeDownCount=1 => end = 99 - 1 + 1 = 99, loop i=99 down to 99 inclusive => one verse. Good.

If takeDownCount=2 => end = 99 - 2 + 1 = 98, loop i=99,98 => two verses.

Edge: if takeDownCount > initial, end becomes <=0, loop will go down to maybe negative, but we probably want to stop at 1. But spec likely expects takeDownCount <= initial. We'll not handle.

